<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-580-873  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 580 873.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Data Based Advisor  Nov 1990 v8 n11 p60(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Data Based Solutions 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Upgrade of SQL query tool offers new dBASE programming constructs.andO;(Quadbase Systems Inc's dQUERY 4.0) (The Complete Comdex Catalog1990) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Quadbase Systems Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   dQUERY 4.0 (Search software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionAdd-In-On SoftwareStructured Query LanguageData Base Management SystemsEnhancementsReport Generators.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Upgrade of SQL Query Tool Offers New dBASE Programming ConstructsandM;SUNNYVALE, CA--Quadbase Systems, Inc. recently released dQUERY 4.0, aninteractive query management system that uses SQL and QBE for ad hoc queriesand report writing.andP;  The new version features dBASE programming constructslike DO WHILE...ENDDO, IF...THEN...ELSE...ENDIF, and @...SAY...GET...READ.andO;It also includes an enhanced report writer and menu-design facility forsetting up query reporting systems.andM;The new version consists of a multi-user database engine, an ANSI Level2-compatible SQL command interface, a QBE interface, and a report writer.andP;  Itallows users to query dBASE and Lotus 1-2-3 files and generate reports.andP;  Itcan join 1-2-3, dBASE III PLUS, and dBASE IV files transparently and save thequery results in dBASE, 1-2-3, or text file formats.andP;  It imports ASCII filesand can have 100 open files.andM;dQUERY 4.0 has built-in multi-user LAN support--file and record lockingprotocol is handled internally.andP;  It can run simultaneously with or fromwithin dBASE, Clipper, or FoxPro applications.andP;  It requires DOS 3.1 (orabove), 640K RAM, and hard disk and runs on any DOS 3.1-compatible LAN.andM;It's priced at $195.andM;For more information, contact Quadbase Systems, Inc., (408) 738-6989, fax(408) 738-6980.andO;</TEXT></DOC>